Fix task execution sequence issue with the UI,CTET-5850,83277,Task,Done,CTET,Core Test Engineering Technology ,software,Joe.Wardwell,5e6aa6b89abcc30ce60ca4ef,,,Major,Done,Seun Osiyemi,60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9,Seun Osiyemi,60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9,Seun Osiyemi,60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9,27/Sep/24 12:20 PM,27/Sep/24 2:14 PM,02/Oct/24 1:36 PM,27/Sep/24 2:14 PM,,0,"I observed that after a failed test, the teardown task starts. But the next task starts before this teardown task is complete.
The setup task also runs in-between the running task. I raised the issue of tasks overlapping each other to the SW team. See the screenshot of the logs below:
The task (E-STOP test) then shortly failed after due to an error where “the handle passed to the function was not valid”.
The issue and more details about it are reported here: [[MFS-10] Stop the UI from skipping tests in the sequence after a task execution fails. - Jira (atlassian.net)
column4: *_10001_*:*_1_*:*_0,"27/Sep/24 2:11 PM;60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9;Raaga determined the task failed because the UDS clients were closed after the teardown task. The teardown task is run at the end of the test sequence. It also runs after a failed task execution, so the UDS clients were closed before the next task which caused the sequence to fail and skip to the teardown task. The setup task which should have re-initialized the UDS clients before the next task in the sequence but did not because it was mapped to the already closed client.

column1: To resolve this, the {{InitializeUDSClient}}function was created in uds.go , which can be used to initialize the UDS client for the first time on all devices. This function was called in setup.go instead of {{GetMantaUDSClient}},{{GetInverterUDSClient}} and {{GetBmuUDSClient }}functions to initialize the UDS clients.
See the function here: [https://github.com/generacclean/voltron/commit/949c4e7c4255d921129ba1aae9e6addf6ecda425#diff-cae655b494b39f1df8488a4898412a3e151f96248b4915e1156f96ac6e06bee6
column3: smart-link]

column1: Updated look on how the UDS clients are initialized in setup.go:
*Before:*
{noformat}   // Initialize UDS Clients
_, err = tester.GetMantaUDSClient(s.Config)
if err != nil {
return plugin.TaskError(fmt.Errorf(""%s"", ""failed_to_initialize_uds_client:""+err.Error()))
_, err = tester.GetInvUDSClient(s.Config)
if err != nil {
return plugin.TaskError(fmt.Errorf(""%s"", ""failed_to_initialize_uds_client:""+err.Error()))
_, err = tester.GetBmuUDSClient(s.Config)
if err != nil {
return plugin.TaskError(fmt.Errorf(""%s"", ""failed_to_initialize_uds_client:""+err.Error()))
}{noformat}
*After:*
{noformat}    // Initialize UDS Clients
// Manta.
if err = tester.InitializeUDSClient(s.Config, common.Manta); err != nil {
return plugin.TaskError(fmt.Errorf(""%s"", ""failed_to_initialize_uds_client:""+err.Error()))
// Inverter.
if err = tester.InitializeUDSClient(s.Config, common.Inverter); err != nil {
return plugin.TaskError(fmt.Errorf(""%s"", ""failed_to_initialize_uds_client:""+err.Error()))
// BMU.
if err = tester.InitializeUDSClient(s.Config, common.BMU); err != nil {
return plugin.TaskError(fmt.Errorf(""%s"", ""failed_to_initialize_uds_client:""+err.Error()))

}{noformat}",27/Sep/24 2:14 PM;60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9;This was tested and validated to address the issue. Now the sequence will continue despite failed tasks within the sequence.,78310,24-Q2-KR7.1: Voltron Runs 80% Automated Tests,Done,27/Sep/24 2:14 PM
